	propagation delay. The system operates as follows. At the start of
	a call, a mobile unit is quasi-synchronised through feedback control
	from the base station. The mobile unit then maintains synchronous
	status without any further base station feedback. The degree of the
	quasi-synchronous accuracy is determined by a clock in mobile units.
